2Fcid%2F2006264%5C%22%3Eeducators%20have%20accused%20the%20government%20of%20interfering%20with%20the%20autonomy%20of%20HEIs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPosters%20and%20compliance%20reports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20education%20ministry%20has%20asked%20institutions%20to%20put%20out%20%E2%80%98Viksit%20Bharat%E2%80%99%20posters%20with%20pictures%20of%20Modi%20at%20the%20programme%20venues.%20The%20ministry%20also%20wants%20the%20institutions%20under%20its%20control%20to%20send%20compliance%20reports%20after%20the%20event%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fahead-of-poll-code-centre-asks-higher-educational-institutions-to-screen-pm-modis-class%2Fcid%2F2006264%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20as%20well%20as%20the%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20(UGC)%20have%20issued%20a%20standard%20operating%20procedure%20(SOP)%20and%20a%20background%20note%20for%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20event%20to%20all%20universities%2C%20including%20state-level%20universities%20and%20private%20universities%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20its%20letter%20to%20vice-chancellors%20of%20these%20institutions%2C%20the%20UGC%20has%20attached%20the%20designs%20of%20five%20posters%20that%20they%20are%20required%20to%20put%20out%20at%20the%20venues.%20The%20posters%20mention%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20Techade%3A%20Chips%20for%20Viksit%20Bharat%E2%80%9D%20and%20carry%20pictures%20of%20Modi%20laying%20the%20foundation%20stone%20for%20the%20semiconductor%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20posters%20related%20to%20the%20event%20are%20attached.%20It%20is%20requested%20to%20disseminate%20the%20information%20about%20the%20programme%20among%20the%20students%20and%20encourage%20them%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20event%20leading%20to%20the%20vision%20of%20Viksit%20Bharat%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20by%20UGC%20secretary%20Manish%20Joshi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fahead-of-poll-code-centre-asks-higher-educational-institutions-to-screen-pm-modis-class%2Fcid%2F2006264%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20background%20note%20shared%20with%20institutions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fahead-of-poll-code-centre-asks-higher-educational-institutions-to-screen-pm-modis-class%2Fcid%2F2006264%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CStudents%20and%20youths%20are%20key%20stakeholders%20of%20this%20endeavour%2C%20therefore%2C%20all%20the%20Universities%2FHEIs%20shall%20make%20necessary%20arrangement%20and%20ensure%20that%20all%20students%2C%20especially%20of%20STEM%20and%20technical%20disciplines%20participate%20in%20above%20programme.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20top-down%20approach%20from%20the%20government%20on%20institutions.%20It%20is%20purely%20a%20propaganda%20programme%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20Researchers%20and%20faculty%20members%20are%20supposed%20to%20focus%20on%20academic%20activities.%20But%20the%20government%20wants%20them%20to%20do%20propaganda%2C%E2%80%9D%20Abha%20Dev%20Habib%2C%20a%20faculty%20member%20at%20Miranda%20House%20College%20said%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20the%20directives%20%E2%80%9Cpolitically%20motivated%E2%80%9D%20and%20wrong%2C%20Ashok%20Agrawal%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20executive%20council%20of%20Delhi%20University%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20brazen%20wrong%20action%20by%20the%20government%20to%20force%20institutions%20to%20divert%20their%20energy%20on%20a%20politically%20motivated%20event.%20The%20institutions%20are%20autonomous.%20They%20have%20the%20power%20to%20ignore%20such%20directions.%20But%20the%20institutions%20are%20unlikely%20to%20ignore%20as%20the%20government%20would%20victimise%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fahead-of-poll-code-centre-asks-higher-edu