Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPost%20The%20Post-WWII%20Global%20Order%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20slow%20disintegration%20of%20the%20post-World%20War%20II%20global%20order%20has%20given%20ample%20space%20to%20non-state%20armed%20groups%20to%20not%20just%20rekindle%20their%20own%20political%20and%20ideological%20aims%20but%20also%20get%20access%20to%20more%20institutional%20frameworks%2C%20such%20as%20those%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20clubhouse%2C%20the%20Security%20Council%20(UNSC).%20Recent%20reports%20in%20some%20sections%20of%20regional%20media%20in%20West%20Asia%20have%20suggested%20that%20a%20meeting%20took%20place%20in%20Doha%20between%20Ismail%20Haniyeh%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20Hamas's%20political%20bureau%2C%20and%20Cao%20Xiaolin%2C%20China's%20ambassador%20to%20Qatar.%20Haniyeh%20reportedly%20praised%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchina-calls-for-peace-conference-on-gaza-as-israel-hamas-war-rages-4867251%5C%22%3EChina's%20role%20and%20stand%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20UN%20on%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%2C%20while%20also%20highlighting%20Beijing's%20humanitarian%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Russia%20also%20recently%20hosted%20a%20congregation%20of%20Palestinian%20groups%2C%20which%20included%20representation%20from%20both%20Hamas%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20Islamic%20Jihad.%20Russia's%20foreign%20minister%2C%20Sergei%20Lavrov%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20this%20meet%20reiterated%20his%20country's%20support%20for%20a%20unified%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organisation%2C%20an%20effort%20that%20would%20see%20Hamas%20try%20to%20work%20with%20Fatah%2C%20a%20Palestinian%20movement%20it%20has%20fought%20against%20over%20political%20and%20ideological%20differences.%20Nonetheless%2C%20the%20question%20is%20not%20so%20much%20about%20Hamas%20here%20but%20Russia's%20aim%20and%20role%2C%20considering%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Moscow%20has%20hosted%20Palestinian%20groups%20since%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia%20And%20China%20Want%20To%20Establish%20New%20Narratives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20US-led%20talks%20fail%20to%20deliver%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20and%20civilian%20deaths%20rise%20rapidly%2C%20for%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20this%20is%20the%20perfect%20time%20to%20puncture%20narratives%20in%20and%20around%20Western%E2%80%94and%2C%20more%20specifically%2C%20US-led%E2%80%94global%20power%20and%20security%20blueprints.%20Both%20Beijing%20and%20Moscow%20also%20have%20good%20relations%20with%20countries%20like%20Iran%2C%20a%20primary%20patron%20of%20Hamas%2C%20and%20Qatar%2C%20which%20hosts%20the%20political%20office%20of%20Hamas%2C%20offering%20mediation%20options.%20All%20this%20is%20accentuated%20by%20a%20deepening%20wish%20of%20middle-power%20states%20to%20chart%20their%20own%20strategic%20autonomy%20and%20not%20side%20with%20specific%20geopolitical%20camps%20or%20alliances.%20This%20was%20also%20seen%20during%20the%20initial%20stages%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20when%20long-standing%20allies%20of%20the%20US%20in%20West%20Asia%20hesitated%20to%20vote%20against%20Russia%20at%20the%20UN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20just%20Hamas%20that%20is%20benefiting%20from%20this.%20The%20Taliban%2C%20now%20close%20to%20three%20years%20in%20power%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20is%20also%20chiselling%20away%20at%20any%20prevailing%20idea%20that%20it%20is%20an%20%E2%80%98isolated'%2C%20hermit%20state.%20At%20a%20recent%20graduation%20ceremony%20of%20religious%20students%20in%20Kabul%2C%20the%20Taliban's%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20for%20Political%20Affairs%2C%20Mawlawi%20Abdul%20Kabir%2C%20highlighted%20that%20the%20Islamic%20Emirate%20is%20in%20%E2%80%9Cpractical%20engagement%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20world%20and%20not%20in%20isolation.%20This%20was%20in%20parallel%20to%20Neda%20Mohammed%20Nadim%2C%20the%20acting%20Minister%20for%20Higher%20Education%2C%20saying%20that%20Islamic%20scholars%20(%3Ci%3Eulema%3C%2Fi%3E)%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20preserve%20the%20Islamic%20system.%20Both%20these%20positions%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20pushback%20by%20the%20Taliban%20against%20Western%E2%80%94and%20UN-led%E2%80%94demands%20on%20issues%20such%20as%20women's%20education%20and%20rights.%C2%A0The%20group%C2%A0sat%20out%20the%20UN%20conference%20in%20Qatar%20on%20Afghanistan's%20future%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaliban-Led%20Afghanistan%20No%20More%20An%20'Isolated'%20State%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taliban%20is%20indeed%20engaging%20with%20most%20of%20its%20regional%20neighbours%2C%20including%20India.%20Russia%2C%20despite%20its%20vocal%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20group%2C%20has%20pushed%20ahead%20with%20the%20Moscow%20format%20and%20deals%20with%20them%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%20China%20has%20gone%20further%2C%20with%20Xi%20Jinping%20personally%20accepting%20the%20credentials%20of%20the%20Taliban's%20new%20ambassador%20in%20Beijing%20in%20January.%20China%20is%20today%20Afghanistan's%20biggest%20economic%20partner%20and%20political%20proponent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20an%20increasingly%20divisive%20narrative%20of%20%E2%80%9Cus%20versus%20them%20(West)%E2%80%9D%2C%20both%20Russia%20and%20China%20have%20reoriented%20their%20risk%20assessments%20about%20more%20volatile%20geographies%20and%20issues.%20In%20comparison%2C%20the%209%2F11%20was%20seen%20by%20Russia%20at%20least%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20build%20bridges%20with%20the%20US.%20In%20Afghanistan%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20at%20that%20time%20had%20shared%20intelligence%20and%20even%20logistical%20support%20against%20Al%20Qaeda%20in%20the%20initial%20stages%20of%20the%20military%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFluid%20Friendships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20both%20Russia%20and%20China%20see%20the%20exit%20of%20the%20US%20military%20from%20the%20Eurasian%20region%20as%20a%20bigger%20strategic%20victory%20for%20their%20individual%20and%20collective%20interests%20despite%20often%20having%20conflicting%20opinions%20on%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20The%20same%20trajectory%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20West%20Asia.%20Scholar%20Yun%20Sun%20recently%20said%20that%20China's%20aim%20is%20to%20displace%20and%20not%20necessarily%20replace%20US%20dominance%2C%20and%20Russia's%20interests%20as%20well%20are%20in%20tow%20with%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20midst%20of%20this%C2%A0%3Ci%3Ekautilyan%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eversion%20of%20chaos%20theory%2C%20actors%20that%20thrived%20and%20survived%20on%20the%20peripheries%20of%20international%20relations%20as%20security%20threats%20may%20now%20find%20themselves%20being%20offered%20the%20mic%2C%20chair%2C%20and%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKabir%20Taneja%20is%20a%20Fellow%20with%20the%20Strategic%20Studies%20Programme%20at%20the%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20'The%20ISIS%20Peril%3A%20The%20World's%20Most%20Feared%20Terror%20Group%20and%20its%20Shadow%20on%20South%20Asia'%20(Penguin%20Viking%2C%202019)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710220140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fl9fl1sc_hamas_625x300_11_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-hamas-taliban-are-gaining-from-russia-chinas-growing-influence-5218810%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amid%20an%20increasingly%20divisive%20narrative%20of%20%26quot%3Bus%20versus%20them%20(West)%26quot%3B%2C%20both%20Russia%20and%20China%20have%20reoriented%20their%20risk%20assessments%20about%20more%20volatile%20geographies%20and%20issues%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-hamas-taliban-are-gaining-from-russia