om%2Findia-vs-england-2024%2Fwith-due-respect-to-axar-patel-rahul-dravids-vvs-laxman-remark-on-indian-cricket-team-batting-order-5219570%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rahul%20Dravid%20namedropped%20former%20teammate%20VVS%20Laxman%20while%20explaining%20the%20decision%20to%20include%20Kuldeep%20Yadav%20in%20the%20playing%20XI%20instead%20of%20an%20all-rounder%20option.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ashok%20Lavasa%20Finds%20Modi%20Govt's%20Exclusion%20of%20CJI%20from%20EC%20Appointment%20Panel%20%E2%80%98Hard%20to%20Fathom%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F11%2Fashok-lavasa.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ashok%20Lavasa%2C%20the%20only%20other%20election%20commissioner%20apart%20from%20Arun%20Goel%20who%20resigned%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20despite%20being%20on%20course%20to%20be%20chief%20election%20commissioner%2C%20has%20spoken%20on%20the%20methods%20being%20adopted%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20for%20appointments%20of%20the%20two%20empty%20spots%20in%20the%20EC%2C%20despite%20clear%20instructions%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20establishing%20a%20process%20that%20avoids%20the%20charge%20of%20partisan%2C%20executive-led%20appointments.%20He%20has%20termed%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20exclusion%20of%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Chard%20to%20fathom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Felection-commission-vacancies-moment-of-reckoning-9208292%2F%5C%22%3EHe%20writes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CJust%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20and%20three%20months%20after%20Parliament%20passed%20a%20law%20excluding%20the%20CJI%20from%20the%20committee%2C%20there%20are%20two%20vacancies%20in%20the%20ECI%20and%20the%20time%20to%20test%20the%20law%20and%20its%20spirit%20is%20here.%E2%80%9D%20Lavasa%20writes%20that%20excluding%20the%20CJI%2C%20whom%20he%20notes%2C%20has%20never%20really%20disagreed%20with%20the%20PM%20in%20other%20such%20selections%2C%20creates%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpredetermined%20bias%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20view.%E2%80%9D%20His%20exclusion%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20seem%20like%20an%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20a%20majority%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20consensus%20building.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELavasa%20has%20been%20explicit%20about%20failing%20to%20follow%20why%20the%20government%20initially%20equated%20the%20EC%20and%20the%20CEC%20with%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20but%20later%20displayed%20%E2%80%9Cmuddled%20thinking%E2%80%9D%20having%C2%A0%20apparently%20%E2%80%9Cstruck%20a%20bargain%E2%80%9D%20by%20restoring%20the%20equivalence%20of%20EC%2FCEC%20with%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20but%20then%20mysteriously%20reversing%20the%20parity%20in%20the%20removal%20process%20of%20the%20EC%20and%20CEC%2C%20to%20the%20original%20one%2C%20where%20only%20the%20CEC%20is%20insulated%20from%20routine%20removal%20process%2C%20not%20other%20members%20of%20the%20EC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20writes%20that%20he%20finds%20it%20%E2%80%9Cequally%20confounding%E2%80%9D%20why%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20has%20been%20replaced%20%E2%80%9Cby%20the%20Law%20Minister%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Search%20Committee.%E2%80%9D%20The%20original%20provision%20in%20the%20new%20law%20to%20appoint%20ECs%2C%20provided%20for%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20other%20members%E2%80%A6%20having%20knowledge%20and%20experience%20in%20matters%20relating%20to%20elections.%E2%80%9D%20The%20purpose%20of%20changing%20the%20chairmanship%20and%20dropping%20%E2%80%9Chaving%20knowledge%20and%20experience%20in%20matters%20relating%20to%20elections%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20members%2C%20has%20been%20called%20out%20by%20Lavasa%2C%20as%20he%20says%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20thought%20process%20behind%20the%20other%20provisions%20as%20proposed%20and%20amended%20beats%20my%20bureaucratic%20understanding%2C%20evolved%20during%20four%20decades%20in%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Five%20Reasons%20There's%20a%20Dark%20Cloud%20Over%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20Transparency%20and%20Functioning%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffive-reasons-theres-a-dark-cloud-over-election-commissions-transparency-and-functioning%5C%22%3EFive%20Reasons%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20Dark%20Cloud%20Over%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20Transparency%20and%20Functioning%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELavasa%E2%80%99s%20four%20decades%20in%20government%20should%20have%20ended%20with%20him%20being%20CEC%2C%20but%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20Manila%E2%80%99s%20Asian%20Development%20Bank%20instead%2C%20after%20the%202019%20polls.%20In%20August%202020%2C%20he%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpresident-kovind-accepts-ashok-lavasas-resignation-from-post-of-election-commissioner%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0just%20months%20short%20of%20becoming%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20in%20April%202021.%20His%20resignation%20came%20a%20year%20after%20he%20became%20the%20only%20member%20of%20the%20three-member%20election%20commission%20to%20rule%20that%20Modi%20had%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fec-record-dissent-note-order-lavasa%5C%22%3E%C2%A0violated%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0while%20campaigning%20for%20the%202019%20general%20election.%20His%20demand%20that%20dissent%20notes%20should%20be%20recorded%20in%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20orders%20on%20model%20code%20violations%20was%20rejected%20with%20a%20majority%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0had%20reported%20that%20just%20weeks%20after%20his%20dissent%2C%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20personal%20mobi