94%20Maulana%20Shahabuddin%20Razvi%20Bareilvi%20(%40Shahabuddinbrly)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FShahabuddinbrly%2Fstatus%2F1767183220762939582%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2011%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20in%20categorical%20terms%20that%20CAA%20was%20brought%20in%20to%20provide%20citizenship%20and%20not%20to%20take%20away%20anyone's%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMinorities%20in%20our%20country%2C%20and%20specially%20our%20Muslim%20community%2C%20are%20being%20provoked.%20CAA%20cannot%20snatch%20away%20anyone's%20citizenship%20because%20there%20is%20no%20provision%20in%20the%20Act.%20CAA%20is%20an%20act%20to%20provide%20citizenship%20to%20refugees%20who%20were%20persecuted%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Shah%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%20evening%2C%20the%20Union%20Home%20Ministry%20notified%20rules%20for%20implementation%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%2C%20days%20ahead%20of%20the%20announcement%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA%2C%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20and%20passed%20by%20Parliament%20in%202019%2C%20aims%20to%20provide%20Indian%20citizenship%20to%20persecuted%20non-Muslim%20migrants%20-%20including%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Jains%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Parsis%2C%20and%20Christians%20-%20who%20migrated%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%20and%20arrived%20in%20India%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20applications%20for%20citizenship%20would%20have%20to%20be%20submitted%20in%20a%20completely%20online%20mode%2C%20for%20which%20a%20web%20portal%20has%20been%20provided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20CAA%20by%20Parliament%20in%20December%202019%20and%20its%20subsequent%20Presidential%20assent%2C%20significant%20protests%20erupted%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20The%20implementation%20of%20the%20CAA%2C%20which%20has%20been%20delayed%20for%20over%20four%20years%2C%20necessitated%20the%20formulation%20of%20its%20associated%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20manual%20of%20parliamentary%20procedures%2C%20the%20guidelines%20for%20any%20legislation%20should%20have%20been%20formulated%20within%20six%20months%20of%20receiving%20the%20presidential%20assent%2C%20or%20the%20government%20should%20have%20sought%20an%20extension%20from%20the%20Committees%20on%20Subordinate%20Legislation%20in%20both%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202020%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20has%20been%20regularly%20seeking%20extensions%20from%20the%20parliamentary%20committees%20to%20continue%20the%20process%20of%20framing%20the%20rules%20associated%20with%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20hundred%20individuals%20lost%20their%20lives%20either%20during%20the%20protests%20or%20due%20to%20police%20action%20subsequent%20to%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20law%20in%20Parliament.%20During%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20over%2030%20district%20magistrates%20and%20home%20secretaries%20across%20nine%20states%20have%20been%20authorized%20with%20the%20ability%20to%20confer%20Indian%20citizenship%20to%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%2C%20Parsis%2C%20and%20Christians%20arriving%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Pakistan%20under%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20of%201955.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20annual%20report%20for%202021-22%2C%20between%20April%201%2C%202021%2C%20and%20December%2031%2C%202021%2C%20a%20cumulative%20count%20of%201%2C414%20individuals%20from%20non-Muslim%20minority%20communities%20originating%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%20were%20granted%20Indian%20citizenship%20through%20registration%20or%20naturalization%20under%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%201955.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20of%201955%2C%20Indian%20citizenship%20by%20registration%20or%20naturalization%20is%20granted%20to%20non-Muslim%20minorities%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%20in%20nine%20states%20such%20as%20Gujarat%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Delhi%2C%20and%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20notable%20that%20authorities%20in%20districts%20of%20Assam%20and%20West%20Bengal%2C%20both%20politically%20sensitive%20regions%20on%20this%20matter%2C%20have%20not%20been%20empowered%20with%20these%20citizenship-granting%20authorities%20thus%20far.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710216600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fm977mun_all-india-muslim-jamaat-president-maulana-shahabuddin-razvi-bareilvi_625x300_12_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-muslims-must-welcome-caa-what-all-india-muslim-jamaat-chief-said-5222183%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22All%20India%20Muslim%20Jamaat%20President%20Maulana%20Shahabuddin%20Razvi%20Bareilvi%20said%20he%20welcomed%20the%20CAA%20legislation%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20allay%20fears%20among%20the%20Muslim%20community%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20impact%20their%20citizenship%20status.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-muslims-must-welcome-caa-what-all-india-muslim-jamaat-chief-said-5222183%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-muslims-must-welcome-caa-what-all-india-muslim-jamaat-chief-said-5222183%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%