pan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20written%20in%20Persian.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnchored%20in%20a%20cultural%20and%20social%20milieu%20different%20from%20ours%2C%20these%20texts%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20understood%20through%20the%20conscientious%20interpretation%20of%20historians.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20325px)%2085vw%2C%20325px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171042%2Fbbcddd8c-dca6-4b97-89f2-6af1eb975919.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22325%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171042%2Fbbcddd8c-dca6-4b97-89f2-6af1eb975919.jpg%20771w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171042%2Fbbcddd8c-dca6-4b97-89f2-6af1eb975919-193x300.jpg%20193w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171042%2Fbbcddd8c-dca6-4b97-89f2-6af1eb975919-658x1024.jpg%20658w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701122%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22506%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIlluminated%20manuscript%20of%20%E2%80%98Bustan%E2%80%99%20by%20Saadi%20Shirazi%2C%20copied%20by%20Kashmiri%20calligrapher%20Abul%20Hassan%20Rizvi%20in%201505%20AD.%20Picture%3A%20Hakim%20Sameer%20Hamdani%20(2024).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20wider%20availability%20of%20their%20English%20translations%20on%20the%20internet%20have%20allowed%20for%20them%20to%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSagasofBharat%2Fstatus%2F1730693846387011594%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emined%20for%20particular%20anecdotes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20stories%20that%20are%20removed%20from%20their%20original%20contexts%20and%20repurposed%20to%20shore%20up%20narratives%20they%20were%20not%20originally%20meant%20to%20serve.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMuslim%20structures%2C%20Hindu%20walls%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20attention%20was%20first%20drawn%20to%20it%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%20when%20a%20popular%20rightwing%20handle%20%E2%80%98True%20Indology%E2%80%99%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20tweeted%20out%20a%20thread%20(now%20deleted)%20on%20Khanqah-e-Moula%20mosque%20in%20Srinagar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20accompanied%20with%20the%20claim%20that%20Khanqah%2C%20whose%20foundation%20was%20laid%20in%20the%2014th%20century%20by%20an%20Iranian%20Sufi%20mystic%20Mir%20Sayyid%20Ali%2C%20was%20constructed%20on%20a%20razed%20Hindu%20temple.%20Although%20the%20handle%20posted%20passages%20from%20a%20400-year-old%20Persian%20text%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBaharistani%20Shahi%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20corroborate%20the%20claim%2C%20he%20mis-identified%20his%20source%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZakhiratul%20Muluk%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%2014th%20century%20political%20treatise%20composed%20by%20Sayyid%20Ali%20that%20ironically%20has%20no%20details%20about%20any%20of%20his%20undertakings%20in%20Kashmir.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%20origins%20of%20Khanqah%20in%20Srinagar%20is%20not%20a%20recent%20development%20though.%20From%20Walter%20Lawrence%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EValley%20of%20Kashmir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1895)%20to%20Pandit%20Anand%20Koul%E2%80%99s%20felicitously%20written%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EArcheological%20Remains%20in%20Kashmir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(1935)%2C%20a%20number%20of%20books%20authored%20around%20late%2019th%20and%20early%2020th%20centuries%20appear%20to%20have%20mentioned%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECiting%20government%20records%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fpaperback%2F9780691116884%2Fhindu-rulers-muslim-subjects%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehistorian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Mridu%20Rai%20refers%20to%20a%201924%20protest%20by%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20demanding%20a%20right%20to%20%E2%80%9Cerect%20a%20covering%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20shrine%2C%20reaffirming%20their%20historical%20attachment%20to%20the%20Muslim%20shrine%20that%20was%20once%20a%20temple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20controversial%20provenance%20of%20Sayyid%20Ali%E2%80%99s%20hermitage%20in%20Srinagar%20is%20elaborately%20explained%20in%20the%20four%20volume%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-i-Hasan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1887)%20by%20Peer%20Hasan%20Shah%2C%20a%20celebrated%2019th%20century%20Kashmiri%20historian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Hasan%E2%80%99s%20telling%2C%20the%20demolished%20temple%20housed%20%E2%80%9C120%20icons%20of%20Mahadeva%E2%80%9D%20and%20belonged%20to%20a%20monk%20named%20Shahpur.%20He%20narrates%20a%20story%20of%20an%20encounter%20between%20Sayyid%20Ali%20and%20the%20monk%20in%20which%20both%20engage%20in%20a%20competitive%20display%20of%20miraculous%20feats.%20The%20monk%20loses%20out%20and%20embraces%20Islam.%20The%20temple%20is%20destroyed%2C%20and%20a%20mosque%20is%20erected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20dissonance%20between%20Persian%20texts%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20version%20of%20story%20is%20incompatible%20with%20an%20earlier%20description%20of%20the%20place%20mentioned%20in%20an%20endowment%20deed%20signed%20by%20Mir%20Sayyid%20Ali%E2%80%99s%20son%20when%20he%20presided%20over%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20hermitage%20in%20late%2014th%20century.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDated%201395%2C%20and%20preserved%20by%20the%20custodians%20of%20Khanqah%2C%20the%20covenant%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20a%20temple%2C%20but%20adds%20that%20the%20dwelling%20place%20of%20Qutubuddin%20Shahmir%2C%20the%20Kashmiri%20ruler%20at%20that%20time%2C%20was%20dismantled%20to%20accommodate%20the%20hermitage.%20The%20document%20also%20refers%20to%20the%20place%20before%20the%20mosque%20as%20a%20land%20measuring%20%E2%80%9C308%20yards%20in%20length%20and%20120%20yards%20in%20breath%E2%80%9D%20that%20was%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20a%20fence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20Hasan%20is%20concocting%20the%20account.%20Instead%2C%20he%20draws%20on%20previous%20Persian%20works%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWaqiat-i-Kashmir%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1765)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETohfat-ul-Ahbab%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1642)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-e-Haider%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(1620)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBaharistani%20Shahi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1614)%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20which%20have%20reproduced%20the%20story%20of%20the%20monk%20told%20originally%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-e-Sayeed%20Ali%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1579).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWritten%20nearly%20two%20centuries%20after%20the%20khanqah%20was%20built%2C%20this%2016th%20century%20manuscript%20forms%20the%20earliest%20extant%20source%20for%20this%20claim.%20But%20now%2C%20new%20historical%20scholarship%20is%20putting%20in%20perspective%20the%20contents%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-e-Sayeed%20Ali%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20allowing%20us%20to%20fully%20decipher%20the%20intent%20and%20purpose%20of%20these%20medieval%20Muslim%20hagiographies.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20fresh%20effort%20to%20unknot%20history%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbdul%20Qaiyum%20Rafiqi%2C%20a%20veteran%20scholar%20of%20Persian%20studies%2C%20was%20first%20to%20observe%20that%20the%20levitating%20monk%20story%20featuring%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-e-Sayeed%20Ali%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20reworking%20of%20similar%20account%20mentioned%20in%20Ibn%20Battuta%E2%80%99s%20travelogue%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Rihla%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1355)%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20borrowed%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFawaid-ul-Fuad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20collection%20of%20sayings%20of%20the%20saint%20Nizamuddin%20Awliya%20of%20Delhi%2C%20compiled%20probably%20at%20the%20turn%20of%2013th%20century.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20324px)%2085vw%2C%20324px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11170653%2Funnamed-3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22324%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11170653%2Funnamed-3.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11170653%2Funnamed-3-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11170653%2Funnamed-3-768x1024.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701120%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20destruction%20of%20temples%20and%20%E2%80%9Cchastising%20the%20infidels%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20a%20popular%20theme%20with%20Persian%20chronicles%20and%20hagiologists%20in%20general%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rafiqi%20writes%20in%20a%20100%20page%20long%20introduction%20to%20the%20second%20edition%20of%20his%20meticulous%20English%20translation%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-e-Sayeed%20Ali%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20was%20released%20recently%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FHistory-Kashmir-Tarikh-i-Kashmir-Saiyid-Ali%2Fdp%2FB001TEALUA%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGulshan%20Books%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERafiqi%20has%20gone%20beyond%20translating%20the%2016th%20century%20manuscript.%20He%20has%20engaged%20with%20the%20text%20very%20critically%20to%20the%20point%20that%20a%20number%20of%20assertions%20originating%20from%20it%20are%20called%20into%20question.%20Those%20include%20the%20claims%20that%20the%2015th%20century%20Kashmiri%20Sultan%20Zayn-ul-Abidin%20was%20taken%20as%20a%20prisoner%20by%20Timur%3B%20or%20that%20Shihabuddin%20Shahmir%2C%20an%20earlier%20Muslim%20Sultan%2C%20expanded%20the%20Kashmiri%20kingdom%20to%20as%20far%20as%20Iran%20and%20imprisoned%20Feroz%20Shah%20Tughlaq%20of%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20critical%20approach%20is%20consistent%20with%20his%20previous%20work%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESufism%20in%20Kashmir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0in%20which%20Rafiqi%20explains%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20how%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKhat-e-Irshad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Letter%20of%20Guidance)%2C%20mentioned%20first%20in%2017th%20century%20hagiological%20text%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFutuhati%20Kubrawiya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20has%20a%20doubtful%20authenticity.%20A%20local%20Sufi%20practice%20(in%20vogue%20at%20least%20till%20mid%2020th%20century)%20of%20holding%20a%20penitent%20religious%20procession%20between%20Khanqah-e-Moula%20in%20Srinagar%20and%20the%20shrine%20of%20Sheikh%20Noor-ud-Din%20in%20Budgam%20is%20rooted%20in%20that%20letter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHistory%20repurposed%20to%20serve%20communal%20politics%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20the%20other%20Persian%20texts%20that%20were%20translated%20into%20English%20in%20recent%20times%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETohfat-ul-Ahbab%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBaharistani%20Shahi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20evaded%20similar%20engagement.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20it%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Frjvraina%2Fstatus%2F1727533311126614332%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecommon%20to%20find%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20content%20from%20these%20texts%20being%20siphoned%20towards%20social%20media%20or%20even%20big%20screens%20to%20serve%20divisive%20political%20ends.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fmedieval-tyrants-and-politicised-interpretations-news-191786%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKashmir%20Files%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0invokes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAhbab%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20make%20sweeping%20claims%20about%20Kashmir%2C%20Islam%20and%20its%20Muslim%20inhabitants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20denying%20that%20persecution%20of%20non-Muslims%20took%20place%20in%20Kashmir%20during%20medieval%20times.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERajatarangini%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20Jonaraja%2C%20a%20more%20authoritative%20Sanskrit%20source%2C%20gives%20reliable%20accounts%20of%20Sikander%20Shahmir%2C%20the%20ruler%20and%20his%20deputy%20Suhabhatta%20as%20they%20laid%20waste%20to%20the%20temples%2C%20and%20presided%20over%20a%20campaign%20of%20forcible%20conversion%20to%20Islam%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctwice%20born.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAhbab%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Erecounts%20stories%20of%20Nurbakshi%20Sufi%20missionaries%20pulling%20down%20at%20least%2056%20temples%20in%20Kashmir%2C%2022%20of%20which%20the%20translator%20Kashinath%20Pandit%20is%20accurately%20able%20to%20trace%20in%20the%2012th%20century%20historical%20text%20Kalhana%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERajatarangini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20implying%20that%20these%20accounts%20are%20not%20exaggerations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20354px)%2085vw%2C%20354px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171142%2F1a7e5707-01fa-4e5d-a1ff-379644a9e7b1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22354%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171142%2F1a7e5707-01fa-4e5d-a1ff-379644a9e7b1.jpg%20783w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171142%2F1a7e5707-01fa-4e5d-a1ff-379644a9e7b1-196x300.jpg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171142%2F1a7e5707-01fa-4e5d-a1ff-379644a9e7b1-668x1024.jpg%20668w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701123%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22543%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIlluminated%20manuscript%20of%20%E2%80%98Bustan%E2%80%99%20by%20Saadi%20Shirazi%2C%20copied%20by%20Kashmiri%20calligrapher%20Abul%20Hassan%20Rizvi%20in%201505%20AD.%20Picture%3A%20Hakim%20Sameer%20Hamdani%20(2024).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20when%20mapped%20against%20the%20larger%20trajectory%20of%20the%20Sultanate%20period%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20these%20episodes%20strike%20more%20as%20interludes%20(that%20are%20deeply%20enmeshed%20with%20the%20processes%20of%20consolidating%20political%20power)%20than%20as%20consistent%20state%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20idea%20of%20syncretic%20past%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20vocabulary%20of%20Jonaraja%2C%20the%20author%20of%20Sanskrit%20text%2C%20while%20he%20describes%20Sikander%E2%80%99s%20temple%20breaking%20spree%20is%20also%20interesting%20because%20he%20likens%20the%20Muslim%20king%20to%20Harsha%20Deva%2C%20a%20previous%20Hindu%20ruler%20of%2011th%20century%20who%20is%20also%20known%20for%20his%20iconoclasm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20remarkable%20that%20he%20isn%E2%80%99t%20distinguishing%20Sikander%20by%20his%20Muslim%20faith%20(that%20colonial%20Indologists%20would%20later%20do)%2C%20and%20admonishes%20him%20and%20Harsha%20Deva%20in%20equal%20measure.%20Jonaraja%20also%20legitimises%20the%20Muslim%20Shahmirid%20rule%20over%20Kashmir%20by%20connecting%20the%20pedigree%20of%20its%20first%20Sultan%20to%20Arjuna%20of%20the%20Hindu%20war%20epic%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMahabharata%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20proclaiming%20that%20he%20was%20blessed%20by%20a%20Hindu%20deity%20in%20his%20dream.%20Of%202%2C150%20verses%20that%20Srivara%2C%20another%20Hindu%20chronicler%20of%20Kashmir%20writes%2C%20800%20alone%20extol%20the%20Muslim%20ruler%20of%20that%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJonaraja%20recalls%20an%20episode%20when%20Shihabuddin%20Shahmir%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20minister%20Udayashri%20recommended%20that%20the%20Sultan%20must%20melt%20a%20brass%20image%20of%20Buddha%20to%20mint%20new%20coins%20as%20the%20treasury%20had%20been%20emptied.%20But%20the%20king%20remonstrates%20him%20saying%20he%20does%20not%20want%20to%20be%20remembered%20as%20someone%20who%20%E2%80%9Cplundered%20the%20image%20of%20God.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20shows%20that%20early%20Muslim%20rule%20in%20Kashmir%20was%20characterised%20by%20a%20spirit%20of%20tolerance.%20Thus%2C%20the%20claim%20made%20200%20years%20later%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETarikh-e-Haider%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20ascribing%20the%20destruction%20of%20a%20temple%20in%20Bijbehara%20to%20Shihabuddin%2C%20naturally%20becomes%20contestable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20nuances%2C%20that%20stand%20in%20sharp%20relief%20to%20the%20communally-loaded%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FArya_Anviksha_%2Fstatus%2F1753442107878977707%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emodern%20day%20rhetoric%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20also%20pervade%20the%20long%20list%20of%20Persian%20texts%20composed%20in%20Kashmir%20during%20the%20Muslim%20rule.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EShahi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Epay