Ahmad%2C%20a%20poet%20laureate%20at%20the%20Shahmirid%20court%20who%20had%20translated%20it%20into%20Persian.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Chitralekha%20Zutshi%20observes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fkashmirs-contested-pasts-9780199481347%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20her%20book%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EContested%20Pasts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Persian%20texts%20are%20not%20only%20dialogically%20connected%20with%20its%20Sanskrit%20histories%2C%20but%20also%20carry%20their%20unique%20imprint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20irony%20of%20%E2%80%98decolonisation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%2C%20however%2C%20the%20colonial%20historiography%20led%20by%20European%20scholars%20such%20as%20H.H.%20Wilson%20and%20Georg%20B%C3%BChler%20that%20accelerated%20the%20periodisation%20of%20Kashmiri%20history%20into%20the%20categories%20of%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim.%20It%20had%20the%20effect%20of%20deracinating%20the%20Sanskrit%20texts%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERajatarangini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVishnudharmottara%20Purana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20localised%20context%2C%20suturing%20them%20to%20notions%20of%20an%20overriding%20Hindu%20antiquity%20that%20bound%20Kashmir%20with%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20refashioning%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERajatarangini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20expression%20of%20Indic%20civilisational%20spirit%2C%20Zutshi%20argues%2C%20elided%20its%20place%20within%20the%20Persian%20historical%20tradition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEventually%2C%20the%20Persian%20historical%20tradition%20declined%20and%20the%20manuscripts%20were%20scavenged%20to%20fish%20out%20anecdotes%20that%20appeared%20to%20re-inscribe%20what%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FThe-Syncretic-Traditions-of-Islamic-Religious-Architecture-of-Kashmir-Early%2FHamdani%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367744298%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Earchitect%20and%20historian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Hakim%20Sameer%20Hamdani%20calls%20a%20%E2%80%9Cparadigm%20of%20conquest%20and%20domination%E2%80%9D%20which%20became%20(and%20wrongly%20so)%20a%20frame%20of%20reference%20against%20which%20the%20Muslim%20edifices%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20such%20as%20Khanqah-e-Moula%20were%20judged.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20sense%2C%20Rafiqi%E2%80%99s%20rigorous%20exegesis%20of%20Sayeed%20Ali%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Etarikh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reverses%20some%20of%20the%20excesses%20of%20the%20colonial%20Indology%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20taking%20a%20leaf%20from%2C%20paradoxically%2C%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdecolonise%E2%80%9D%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EShakir%20Mir%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Srinagar-based%20journalist.%20He%20tweets%20at%20%40shakirmir.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710160252000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11171803%2FCopy-of-Copy-of-Lead-image-size-6.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-kashmirs-medieval-persian-tarikhs-were-mined-for-modern-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anchored%20in%20a%20cultural%20and%20social%20milieu%20different%20from%20ours%2C%20these%20texts%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20understood%20through%20conscientious%20interpretation%20of%20historians.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-kashmirs-medieval-persian-tarikhs-were-mined-for-modern-politics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parliament%20Today%20a%20Pale%20Shadow%20of%20What%20it%20Used%20to%20Be%2C%20Executive%20No%20L