ording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Sandeep%20Mehta%20were%20hearing%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20state%20of%20Maharashtra.%20The%20bench%20pointed%20out%20that%20Saibaba%20had%20his%20co-accused%20had%20been%20acquitted%20twice%2C%20by%20two%20different%20benches%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20told%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20S.V.%20Raju%2C%20appearing%20for%20Maharashtra%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20two%20orders%20of%20acquittal%20by%20two%20different%20benches.%C2%A0%3Ci%3EPrima%20facie%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20we%20find%20that%20the%20judgment%20is%20very%20well-reasoned.%20Since%20on%20an%20earlier%20occasion%2C%20this%20court%20had%20interfered%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20honour%20that.%20Otherwise%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20well-reasoned%20judgment%20by%20the%20high%20court.%20In%20ordinary%20course%2C%20we%20would%20not%20have%20entertained%20this%20appeal.%20The%20parameters%20of%20interference%20with%20acquittal%20orders%20are%20very%20limited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20hard-earned%20acquittal.%20How%20many%20years%20has%20the%20man%20spent%20in%20jail%3F%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Mehta%20added%2C%20followed%20by%20Justice%20Gavai%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20law%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20presumption%20of%20innocence.%20Once%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20order%20of%20acquittal%2C%20that%20presumption%20gets%20fortified.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsaibaba-acquittal-from-lack-of-sanction-to-dodgy-evidence-high-court-judgment-tears-into-states-case%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20judgment%20had%20criticised%20both%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20probe%20and%20the%20trial%20court%20judgment%20finding%20the%20men%20guilty.%20Justice%20Vinay%20G.%20Joshi%20and%20Justice%20